To install simply create a mysql database and import sql/mhd2.sql

mysqladmin -u root -p create mhd2
mysql -u root -p mhd2 < mhd2.sql

the name of the database is not a mandatory
You mut edit include/config.inc.php to fit your needs
Next you have to configure apache to see the mhd2 directory and go with a browser to  http://localhost/mhd2 (for example)

The default login/password is admin/admin !!! CHANGE IT AFTER INSTALL !!!
To modify parameters you can go to the config entry in the menu
The repository, where files for tickets, customers and contracts are stored, is relative to the base_url and must have three subdirectories "customer", "ticket" and "contract"

